<h2>RESPONSIBILITIES/ROLES</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Provide in-person, telephone, and e-mail assistance (information and guidance) to parents regarding special education procedures for school-age children with disabilities.</li>
  <li>Develop and present workshops in communities throughout the state for parents of school-age children with disabilities and professionals.</li>
  <li>Assist in public informational and educational activities by providing presentations to various organizations and professional groups.</li>
  <li>Research and write clear, informative materials on special education and closely related topics.&nbsp;</li>
  <li>Other activities as required.</li>
</ol>
<hr />
<h2>EXPERIENCE/BACKGROUND SKILLS</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Ability to work well with others and interest in relating to parents of children with disabilities.</li>
  <li>Experience in public speaking, workshop presentations, and assisting others on the telephone and over e-mail.</li>
  <li>Experience working with individuals in a guidance role.</li>
  <li>Extensive experience and background in research and writing. </li>
  <li>Knowledge of laws and rules related to the education of school-age children, including early childhood, with disabilities.</li>
  <li>Ability to keep accurate records and collect data for evaluation purposes through using a database.</li>
  <li>Experience using computers and various programs</li>
  <li>Ability to provide own transportation and flexibility to travel. Workshops are presented during both day time and evening hours, therefore, flexible schedule needed.</li>
  <li>Experience in community service/human service/social service.</li>
  <li>Ability to work with diverse populations.</li>
  <li>Ability to apply analytical skills.</li>
  <li>Excellent organizational skills, ability to meet deadlines.</li>
  <li>College degree or equivalent background gained through training or work experience.</li>
</ol>
<hr />
<p><strong>Salary to be determined  based on experience.</strong></p>
